sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    Title: Stage 2 — CI/CD Pipeline (Hetzner + AWS EKS Hybrid)

    actor DEV as 👨‍💻 Developer
    participant GH as GitHub Actions
    participant ECR as Amazon ECR
    participant GHCR as GH Container<br/>Registry (Hetzner)
    participant EKS as AWS EKS<br/>(US/Regulated)
    participant HETZNER as K3s/Talos<br/>(Hetzner EU)
    participant SM as Secrets Manager<br/>(AWS)
    participant ArgoCD as ArgoCD<br/>(GitOps)

    DEV->>GH: git push main
    GH->>GH: Run tests & security scans

    par Migrate to EKS (US workloads)
        GH->>ECR: docker build + docker push<br/>api-us:v3.0.0
        GH->>SM: Fetch DB credentials
        GH->>SM: Fetch EKS cluster credentials
        GH->>EKS: kubectl apply -f k8s/us-production/
        GH->>EKS: kubectl set image deployment/api-us
        EKS->>EKS: Rolling update US services
        EKS-->>DEV: ✅ US workload deployed
    and Migrate to Hetzner (EU workloads)
        GH->>GHCR: docker build + docker push<br/>api-eu:v3.0.0
        GH->>HETZNER: kubectl set image deployment/api-eu
        HETZNER->>HETZNER: Rolling update EU services
        HETZNER-->>DEV: ✅ EU workload deployed
    end

    rect rgba(0, 100, 0, 0.1)
        Note over GH,EKS: GitOps sync for subsequent commits:
        ArgoCD monitors repo → auto-syncs to EKS
        GitHub Actions triggers K3s push for Hetzner
    end

    DEV->>ArgoCD: Merge to main (EKS)
    ArgoCD->>ArgoCD: Detect drift / sync
    ArgoCD->>EKS: kubectl apply (EKS workloads)
    ArgoCD-->>DEV: ✅ EKS in sync

    Note over SM,HETZNER: Cross-cloud secret sharing:<br/>External Secrets Operator<br/>pulls from AWS SM → injects into Hetzner K8s
